  <front>
    <title>RepSec Non-Reusable Data Extension (NRU)</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ehlers-repsec-nru-00"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="Ehlers" fullname="Ralph Ehlers">
      <organization>PastWipe S.L.</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="14" month="September" year="2025"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>   NRU specifies one-time, cryptographically bound tokens that couple a
   dataset identifier to a requester context.  Replayed or stolen
   datasets fail verification in the RepSec layer, preventing
   unauthorized reuse.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
